{
  "stem": "21626.2",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It seemed so strange to me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But they wormed their way into my heart immediately.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It happened to be my birthday when I arrived.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And there were lashings of wonderful creamy ice cream and strawberries, which made up a lot for that horrible bread and marmalade and salty butter [LAUGHS] I had the day before.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I was very happy with the family.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But I didn't stay long because by the end of July, the threat of war was sort of imminent.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And there was talk of evacuation of the children out of Liverpool.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I did spend, of course, a month in the school, where they looked at me as if I was a creature from out of space because nobody had heard or seen anyone from Czechoslovakia, you know.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And there was-- I, I remember the streets were lined with kids curious to see me.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I remember hearing the sound of my-- the echoes of my feet and Mummy Rainford's feet-- I called her Mummy Rainford and Daddy Rainford, you know, from the word go-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] as they led me, as she led me, you know, to the, to the school.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So just a few weeks after arriving, I had to move again to another family in Southport.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, I picked up English very quickly.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was determined, also, to teach the family Czech, at which I was not so successful.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But my English sister, particularly, was a great teacher and took great pains in explaining things to me.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I went-- when I went to the school, they put me with seven-year-olds because I didn't understand any English.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I didn't like that at all.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But their teacher spoke German.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And though I wouldn't speak, of course I did understand.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
